data.enText: the years of a person's life when they are between 13 and 19 years old
She began writing poetry in her teens .

data.chText: 现年十三四 / 十八九岁
data.enText: to be in your early/late teens

tr: all the numbers that end in -teen
the time of life between the ages of 12 and 20

value.def: If you are in your teens, you are between thirteen and nineteen years old.

example.ex: Most people who smoke began smoking in their teens...
example.tran: 多数烟民从十几岁时就开始抽烟了。

example.ex: My late teens and early twenties were really rough years...
example.tran: 我二十岁前后那几年过得真苦啊。

example.ex: I spent most of my teen years reading diet books.
example.tran: 我青少年时期的大部分时间都用来阅读控制饮食的书籍了。

value.tran: 十几岁，青少年时期(指从 13 岁到 19 岁)

value.def: Teen is used to describe things such as films, magazines, bands, or activities that are aimed at or are done by people who are in their teens.

example.tran: 乔治·卡林主演的青春片

example.ex: Pop isn't pop without huge teen sensations.
example.tran: 不能激起广大青少年热情的流行音乐就不能称其为流行音乐。

value.tran: 面向青少年的;由青少年完成的

value.def: A teen is someone aged between thirteen and nineteen years old.

example.ex: It used to be that any teen who wanted a summer job could get one.
example.tran: 从前，十几岁的孩子到了暑假都能找着活干。

value.tran: 青少年,十几岁的孩子(指从 13 岁到 19 岁)

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, usually use 英国英语通常用 teenager
